%description
Create a pie like plot to visualise if the aim or several aims of a
project is achieved or close to be achieved i.e the aim is achieved when
the point is at the center of the pie plot. Imagine it's like a dartboard
and the center means 100% completeness/achievement. Achievement can also
be understood as 100% coverage. The standard distribution of completeness
allocated in the pie plot is 50%, 80% and 100% completeness.

